---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Astro + Sanity Starter"
  description="A clean Astro starter with an embedded Sanity Studio, Tailwind CSS v4, and Vercel-ready server output."
>
  <main
    class="mx-auto flex min-h-screen max-w-5xl flex-col gap-16 px-6 py-16 sm:px-10"
  >
    <section class="grid gap-8 lg:grid-cols-[minmax(0,1fr)_22rem] lg:items-end">
      <div class="space-y-6">
        <p
          class="text-sm font-semibold uppercase tracking-[0.28em] text-emerald-300"
        >
          Clean Starter
        </p>
        <div class="space-y-4">
          <h1
            class="max-w-3xl text-4xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-white sm:text-6xl"
          >
            Astro + Sanity with an embedded Studio and a Vercel-ready server
            build.
          </h1>
          <p class="max-w-2xl text-lg leading-8 text-zinc-300">
            Use this repo as a starting point for content-driven Astro sites.
            The Sanity Studio lives at <code>/studio</code>, Tailwind is wired
            in, and the starter ships with a minimal schema so the Studio is
            useful on day one.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-4">
          <a
            class="rounded-full bg-emerald-300 px-5 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-zinc-950 transition hover:bg-emerald-200"
            href="/studio"
          >
            Open Studio
          </a>
          <a
            class="rounded-full border border-zinc-700 px-5 py-3 text-sm font-semibold text-zinc-100 transition hover:border-zinc-500 hover:bg-zinc-900"
            href="https://www.sanity.io/docs"
            target="_blank"
            rel="noreferrer"
          >
            Sanity Docs
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="rounded-3xl border border-zinc-800 bg-zinc-900/70 p-6">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-white">Starter includes</p>
        <ul class="mt-4 space-y-3 text-sm text-zinc-300">
          <li>Astro 6 server output with the Vercel adapter</li>
          <li>Embedded Studio at <code>/studio</code></li>
          <li>Tailwind CSS v4 via the Vite plugin</li>
          <li>
            Sanity starter schema with <code>siteSettings</code> and <code
              >page</code>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </section>

    <section class="grid gap-6 md:grid-cols-3">
      <article class="rounded-3xl border border-zinc-800 bg-zinc-900/50 p-6">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-white">1. Configure env</p>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-7 text-zinc-300">
          Copy <code>.env.example</code> to <code>.env</code> and set your Sanity
          project ID and dataset.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="rounded-3xl border border-zinc-800 bg-zinc-900/50 p-6">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-white">2. Start the app</p>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-7 text-zinc-300">
          Run <code>bun run dev</code> and open both the site root and
          <code>/studio</code>.
        </p>
      </article>
      <article class="rounded-3xl border border-zinc-800 bg-zinc-900/50 p-6">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold text-white">3. Allow Studio auth</p>
        <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-7 text-zinc-300">
          Add <code>http://localhost:4321</code> as a CORS origin with credentials
          when Sanity prompts you.
        </p>
      </article>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
